# containr User Guide (EN)

## 1. Overview
- containr is a terminal UI (TUI) for managing Docker/Podman hosts over SSH.
- It provides views for stacks, containers, images, volumes, networks, templates, registries, logs, inspect, themes, and messages.

## 2. Requirements
- Docker or Podman on target hosts, reachable via SSH.
- SSH key access (passwordless recommended).
- Rust toolchain for builds; OS keyring support (macOS Keychain, Linux Secret Service, Windows Credential Manager).
- Default paths:
  - Config: `~/.config/containr/config.json`
  - Registries: `~/.config/containr/registries.json`
  - Templates: `~/.config/containr/templates/{stacks,networks}`

## 3. Layout & Navigation
- Views: Dashboard, Stacks, Containers, Images, Volumes, Networks, Templates, Registries, Inspect, Logs, Help, Messages, Themes.
- Focus: Sidebar ↔ List ↔ Details ↔ Dock (logs), switch with `Tab`/`Shift-Tab`, `b`, `d`.
- Layout: `C-p` toggles split mode (horizontal/vertical) per view.
- Quit: `:q` (with y/n prompt) or `:q!` (immediate).

## 4. Servers & Connections
- Add server:
  - `:server add <name> --target <ssh_target> [--cmd "<docker_cmd>"] [--identity <path>]`
- Select server via sidebar + Enter/shortcut.
- Reconnect: `:server reconnect`
- Shell: `:server shell` (opens remote shell for configured server).

## 5. Stacks
- List in `Stacks` view.
- Actions: start, stop, restart, delete.
- Recreate: `:stack recreate [--pull]`
- Update: `:stack update`

## 6. Containers
- List in `Containers` view.
- Actions: start, stop, restart, delete, logs, inspect, console, mark/unmark.
- Multi-select: mark with Space, actions apply to marked entries.

## 7. Images
- List in `Images` view.
- Actions: remove, untag, inspect.
- Update check: `:image check` (24h TTL).

## 8. Volumes & Networks
- Volumes: remove, inspect, details.
- Networks: remove, inspect.

## 9. Templates (Compose)
- Paths: `~/.config/containr/templates/stacks` and `.../networks`.
- Identity marker: `# containr_template_id=<uuid>` for deploy tracking.
- Deploy: `:template deploy [--recreate] [--pull]`
- Edit: Enter opens editor (`editor_cmd` -> `$EDITOR` -> `vi`).
- Git: template directory supports optional git autocommit.

## 10. Registries & Auth
- File: `registries.json`
- Auth types: `anonymous`, `basic`, `bearer-token`, `github-pat`
- Prefer keyring:
  1. `keyring set containr "<host>/<label>"`
  2. `:registry set <host> secret-keyring "<host>/<label>"`
  3. `:registry set <host> auth basic` / `:registry set <host> user <name>`
- Test: `:registry test <host>`

## 11. Themes
- Switch: `:theme select`
- Files: user overrides under `~/.config/containr/themes/*.json`
- Built-in themes: loaded from `themes/` relative to the bundle/workspace or from system paths like `/usr/share/containr/themes`
- Active theme: `active_theme` in `config.json`

## 12. Messages & Logs
- Open: `C-g` or `:messages`
- Save: `:messages save <path>`
- Docked log panel: `log_dock_enabled` in config

## 13. Image Updates
- Check: `:image check`
- Markers: green=ok, yellow=update, red=error, blue=rate-limit

## 14. Git Autocommit (Templates)
- `:git auto on|off`
- Header indicator: `Commit: auto|manual`

## 15. Configuration
Key fields:
- `servers`, `templates_dir`, `active_theme`, `editor_cmd`
- `git_autocommit`, `git_autocommit_confirm`
- `image_update_concurrency`, `image_update_autocheck`, `image_update_debug`
- `kitty_graphics`, `log_dock_enabled`, `log_dock_height`
- `view_layout`, `keymap`

## 16. Keyboard Shortcuts (excerpt)
- Navigation: `Tab`/`Shift-Tab`, `b`, `d`
- Layout: `C-p`
- Global: `F1` help, `C-g` messages, `C-b` sidebar toggle
- Containers: `C-s`, `C-o`, `C-r`, `C-d`, `C-l`, `C-i`
- Stacks: `C-s`, `C-o`, `C-r`, `C-d`, `C-u`
- Templates: `C-e`, `C-n`, `C-y`, `C-S-Y`

## 17. Troubleshooting
- Connection issues: check `:messages`, `docker_cmd`, SSH identity.
- Red/blue image update status: rate limits or missing digests; configure registry auth.

## 18. Tests
- Local: `cargo test --locked`
- Optional integration: `integration` feature

## 19. Security
- Store secrets in keyring, not plaintext.
- AGE-encrypted secrets are supported as fallback.

